### Which @angular/* package(s) are relevant/related to the feature request?

forms

### Description

The `ControlValueAccessor` interfaces relies on `any` for the typing of its definitions, I would like to be able to strongly type a `ControlValueAccessor`

### Proposed solution

Instead of:
```ts
@Component({ /*...*/ })
class MyComponent implements ControlValueAccessor {
  writeValue(obj: any): void {}
  registerOnChange(fn: any): void {}
  registerOnTouched(fn: any): void {}
  setDisabledState?(isDisabled: boolean): void {}
}
```

I would have liked to be able to write:
```ts
@Component({ /*...*/ })
class MyComponent implements TypedControlValueAccessor<TValue> {
  writeValue(obj: TValue): void {}
  registerOnChange(fn: (value: TValue) => void): void {}
  registerOnTouched(fn: () => void): void {}
  setDisabledState?(isDisabled: boolean): void {}
}
```

### Alternatives considered

This is non blocking and just some qualify of life
If absolutely necessary, I can create another interface acting as an adapter for the non-typed version

